1
00:00:10,030 --> 00:00:11,330
Jiang Zhihao

2
00:00:12,170 --> 00:00:13,470
Go to Japan.

3
00:00:18,430 --> 00:00:20,070
How's the progress

4
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:21,700
on that 30th anniversary toy?

5
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:23,430
We've signed the contract with the manufacturer.

6
00:00:23,430 --> 00:00:24,830
Once we confirm the samples are good,

7
00:00:24,830 --> 00:00:26,600
we can start mass production.

8
00:00:27,270 --> 00:00:28,600
If I remember correctly,

9
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:29,400
isn't the factory owner

10
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,260
an acquaintance of Jiang Zhihao?

11
00:00:33,030 --> 00:00:34,470
But

12
00:00:34,470 --> 00:00:36,800
Guangsheng Toys won the bid fair and square.

13
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,000
They passed all qualification checks.

14
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:45,200
Then let's make sure they have problems.

15
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,570
Don't forget

16
00:00:47,570 --> 00:00:48,770
what you promised me.

17
00:00:49,830 --> 00:00:51,230
Brother Kang said

18
00:00:51,230 --> 00:00:52,900
as long as you handle this well,

19
00:00:52,900 --> 00:00:54,770
you'll get what you deserve.

20
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,400
The toy factory employees said

21
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:03,100
their boss often cuts corners.

22
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:05,600
We're just punishing him early.

23
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,170
You're overthinking things.

24
00:01:07,170 --> 00:01:08,700
Let's change the subject.

25
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,400
I have a gift for you.

26
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,470
Look.

27
00:01:14,530 --> 00:01:16,370
Didn't you want to study in Japan?

28
00:01:16,370 --> 00:01:19,430
I've arranged everything - school and accommodation.

29
00:01:20,470 --> 00:01:21,870
You go first.

30
00:01:21,870 --> 00:01:23,030
Once my temporary assignment comes through,

31
00:01:23,030 --> 00:01:24,500
I'll come find you.

32
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:26,730
So after we're in Japan,

33
00:01:26,730 --> 00:01:28,400
we won't have to meet

34
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:30,400
in secret anymore?

35
00:01:31,670 --> 00:01:32,270
You need to understand

36
00:01:32,270 --> 00:01:33,130
everything you're doing now

37
00:01:33,130 --> 00:01:35,300
will make our future better.

38
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:36,600
You want my dreams to come true too,

39
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:37,630
don't you?

40
00:03:57,970 --> 00:03:58,930
Hello everyone.

41
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:00,700
I'm Deng Yongkuan.

42
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:02,370
First, I'd like to thank

43
00:04:02,370 --> 00:04:03,970
Chairman Jin

44
00:04:03,970 --> 00:04:05,700
of Meiman TV Station.

45
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:08,170
It's an honor to meet everyone here today.

46
00:04:08,170 --> 00:04:09,870
Linlin Breakfast

47
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:13,200
has been in the food industry for decades.

48
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,200
I believe it has already become

49
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:16,570
a part of everyone's daily life.

50
00:04:16,570 --> 00:04:18,230
Today's achievements

51
00:04:18,230 --> 00:04:20,529
are thanks to our Vice President,

52
00:04:20,529 --> 00:04:21,670
Deng Weikang,

53
00:04:21,670 --> 00:04:23,830
and all the staff at Linlin

54
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:25,800
for their persistence and hard work.

55
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,070
I'm truly happy.

56
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:28,270
Thank you all.

57
00:04:34,930 --> 00:04:37,370
Our golden couple in the middle.

58
00:05:04,970 --> 00:05:05,770
Next,

59
00:05:05,770 --> 00:05:08,770
our two companies will have many collaborations.

60
00:05:08,770 --> 00:05:10,400
If reporters have any questions,

61
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,300
we'll answer them one by one.

62
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,570
Hello?

63
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,370
Where is she?

64
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:36,870
She's already checked out.

65
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:38,530
Excuse me, when did she leave?

66
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:40,930
Around 7 or 8 in the morning.

67
00:05:40,930 --> 00:05:41,600
Okay, thank you.

68
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,870
No way.

69
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:46,330
She checked out early. What do we do?

70
00:05:46,330 --> 00:05:47,800
Checked out.

71
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,630
We'll have to take a chance.

72
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,730
What do you mean?

73
00:05:52,730 --> 00:05:54,030
Go find her.

74
00:06:12,970 --> 00:06:14,670
Is it this way?

75
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:31,400
Peizhen.

76
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,470
You guys.

77
00:06:33,470 --> 00:06:34,970
Long time no see.

78
00:06:34,970 --> 00:06:36,370
Can we go in?

79
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:40,670
You must be Peizhen's good colleagues.

80
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:42,030
Right?

81
00:06:42,030 --> 00:06:43,070
You knew she was on vacation

82
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:44,970
and came specially to see her.

83
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:47,100
Come, take a rest.

84
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:49,000
Have some grapes. You brought them.

85
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,070
Okay.

86
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:51,630
Your colleague is really nice.

87
00:06:51,630 --> 00:06:53,500
Look, she brought fruit when she stopped by.

88
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:56,300
And helped us make dumplings.

89
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:57,230
Ma'am.

90
00:06:57,230 --> 00:06:59,170
I'll charge you just 5 yuan per grape.

91
00:06:59,170 --> 00:07:00,530
Make it 10 for you.

92
00:07:00,530 --> 00:07:01,470
You know quality.

93
00:07:01,470 --> 00:07:02,370
Look.

94
00:07:02,370 --> 00:07:03,970
I made all of these.

95
00:07:03,970 --> 00:07:04,870
They look great.

96
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:07,070
They really are well-made.

97
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:08,700
But look at yours.

98
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,730
You've gotten worse.

99
00:07:12,970 --> 00:07:14,170
After you went to Japan,

100
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:16,600
we rarely made dumplings anymore.

101
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,930
That's not true.

102
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,030
Yes, it is.

103
00:07:20,030 --> 00:07:21,470
Let me think.

104
00:07:21,470 --> 00:07:24,030
How many years have you been in Japan now?

105
00:07:24,970 --> 00:07:26,170
After she went to Japan,

106
00:07:26,170 --> 00:07:28,200
I kept saying I would visit her there,

107
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,370
but in the blink of an eye, years have passed,

108
00:07:30,370 --> 00:07:32,770
and I haven't gone even once.

109
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:35,570
Sometimes I wonder

110
00:07:35,570 --> 00:07:36,500
if you're really

111
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:39,570
working in Japan for your company.

112
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:45,100
Maybe I should visit you in Japan next month.

113
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,460
Auntie, that's not possible.

114
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,000
Why not?

115
00:07:55,530 --> 00:07:58,130
Business is really good in Japan right now,

116
00:07:58,130 --> 00:07:59,900
and she's extremely busy with work.

117
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,300
Last time we went to see her,

118
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:03,330
she didn't even have time for us.

119
00:08:03,330 --> 00:08:04,600
That's right.

120
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,330
That busy, huh?

121
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:09,730
Don't you know your daughter by now?

122
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:12,200
She only shares the good news, never the bad.

123
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,730
Don't be fooled by her constant smile.

124
00:08:14,730 --> 00:08:17,100
She takes everything upon herself.

125
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,100
No matter how bad she feels,

126
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:21,170
she'll always say 'I'm fine, I'm good.'

127
00:08:21,170 --> 00:08:23,230
So she's really struggling in Japan.

128
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,470
But she's such a good daughter.

129
00:08:31,470 --> 00:08:34,929
She sends money back to me every month.

130
00:08:34,929 --> 00:08:38,070
Mom knows how hard you all are working.

131
00:08:40,429 --> 00:08:41,830
The soup seems ready.

132
00:08:42,370 --> 00:08:44,330
Take a break and have some fruit.

133
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,800
We'll eat dinner soon.

134
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:47,900
Wait a moment.

135
00:08:53,270 --> 00:08:54,470
Thank you.

136
00:09:00,770 --> 00:09:02,370
Deng Weiyu

137
00:09:02,370 --> 00:09:03,800
About what I promised you,

138
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,270
I'm really sorry.

139
00:09:06,130 --> 00:09:08,230
I have too many concerns to consider.

140
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,430
Alright, I really need to go now.

141
00:09:55,530 --> 00:09:57,230
Hello.

142
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:58,800
You told me

143
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,300
not to be shocked by the news,

144
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,800
that it's all fake.

145
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:06,370
I explained to you before the press conference.

146
00:10:06,370 --> 00:10:08,900
Linlin needs to change her image now,

147
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:11,570
and Xie Jinghan's mother can help with this.

148
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,770
The marriage is just for show.

149
00:10:14,770 --> 00:10:16,770
We won't actually get married.

150
00:10:17,770 --> 00:10:18,500
When we got together,

151
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:19,930
you knew I couldn't go public.

152
00:10:19,930 --> 00:10:21,830
You must feel hurt and sad.

153
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:23,470
I blame myself too.

154
00:10:24,770 --> 00:10:26,300
Sometimes I think

155
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,770
we should break up,

156
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,730
but I just can't do it.

157
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:31,030
I need you.

158
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:33,000
I can't lose you.

159
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,500
I'll come see you

160
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,700
next month.

161
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:38,030
Next week.

162
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:40,100
I think I have three days off next week.

163
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:41,700
It depends on your schedule.

164
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,830
Wishes fulfilled.

165
00:10:47,970 --> 00:10:50,470
Safe travels.

166
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:56,130
Health and peace.

167
00:10:57,330 --> 00:10:58,200
Here, have some.

168
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,600
But what you need

169
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,000
most right now is this one.

170
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:06,900
Keep this good match charm for yourself.

171
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,370
This is for you.

172
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:09,900
Why drag me into this?

173
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:10,800
How old am I now?

174
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,000
What do I need love for?

175
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,570
Keep it for yourself.

176
00:11:16,870 --> 00:11:18,530
This one.

177
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:21,030
Good. Wishes fulfilled.

178
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:26,030
When are you going back to Japan?

179
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:32,000
Maybe I won't go back.

180
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,300
I'll stay with you, okay?

181
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:36,130
Then you won't

182
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:37,870
have to worry about me anymore.

183
00:11:42,130 --> 00:11:44,800
Of course it would be nice if you stayed with me.

184
00:11:48,970 --> 00:11:51,000
But no matter how old you are,

185
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,800
wherever you go,

186
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,630
whatever decisions you make,

187
00:11:55,670 --> 00:11:57,870
Mom will still worry about you.

188
00:12:00,570 --> 00:12:03,200
Mom actually worries too.

189
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:07,730
You're not happy at all.

190
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,730
You just don't let me know.

191
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:14,270
Mom.

192
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,000
So.

193
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:26,670
Since Mom is destined to worry about you for life,

194
00:12:27,570 --> 00:12:29,830
you must be happy.

195
00:12:31,070 --> 00:12:34,600
Don't make any decisions that make you feel wronged.

196
00:12:36,170 --> 00:12:38,430
Mom will always be here,

197
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:40,070
you know?

198
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,200
My darling, prepare some snacks for me.

199
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,270
Mom will make you a cup of tea.

200
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:31,400
Here.

201
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,970
Don't be like that.

202
00:13:33,970 --> 00:13:35,970
Congratulations.

203
00:13:35,970 --> 00:13:37,130
Here, have something sweet.

204
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:38,600
Pink bubbles. Pop!

205
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,200
Thank you all for your blessings.

206
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,830
We've received them all.

207
00:13:41,830 --> 00:13:42,570
Yes.

208
00:13:42,570 --> 00:13:43,770
Here, let's share.

209
00:13:43,770 --> 00:13:45,370
Come on, together.

210
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:47,930
Thank you. Congratulations.

211
00:13:47,930 --> 00:13:49,330
Come.

212
00:13:49,330 --> 00:13:50,470
Weiyu, come here.

213
00:13:50,470 --> 00:13:51,970
Have something sweet.

214
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,930
Is it sugar-free?

215
00:13:53,930 --> 00:13:55,600
Full sugar. Today we only have full sugar.

216
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:57,370
Here, there's more. Come, have a drink.

217
00:13:57,370 --> 00:13:58,570
Drinks, yes.

218
00:13:58,570 --> 00:13:59,800
Everyone come and get some.

219
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:01,130
We only have full sugar today. Don't be shy.

220
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:01,900
Thank you.

221
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:03,930
Come on, help yourself.

222
00:14:03,930 --> 00:14:05,530
Take one.

223
00:14:10,770 --> 00:14:12,070
Let me tell you.

224
00:14:12,070 --> 00:14:13,730
I've looked at many honeymoon destinations.

225
00:14:13,730 --> 00:14:15,170
Let me show you.

226
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:15,970
Just a moment.

227
00:14:16,470 --> 00:14:17,500
The Maldives?

228
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,570
How about we go here?

229
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:30,770
Too cold. Not suitable for a honeymoon.

230
00:14:34,530 --> 00:14:35,400
Deng Weikang.

231
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,770
Long time no see.

232
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:40,900
And you are?

233
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:42,030
No, she's... she's here to congratulate you both.

234
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:43,300
She's a former colleague.

235
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:44,530
You first...

236
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:45,730
What are you doing?

237
00:14:46,170 --> 00:14:47,400
I'm his girlfriend.

238
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,100
We've been dating for many years.

239
00:14:53,370 --> 00:14:54,070
Who is she?

240
00:14:54,070 --> 00:14:54,700
No, let me explain.

241
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:55,830
She's a former colleague.

242
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:56,570
What do you mean 'former'? Weren't you in Japan?

243
00:14:56,570 --> 00:14:57,270
Why did you come back?

244
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:58,370
Weren't you the one who told me to go to Japan?

245
00:14:58,370 --> 00:14:59,400
Yes, but...

246
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,430
Didn't we already agree?

247
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:01,800
That you would just stay in Japan?

248
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,000
What agreement? What's the meaning of showing up suddenly?

249
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,300
What did you agree with me?

250
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,030
Well...

251
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:06,300
You better explain yourself right now.

252
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:06,900
No... who is she?

253
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:08,530
There was a temporary case before, so I...

254
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:10,100
I have our chat history.

255
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:11,730
Look.

256
00:15:11,730 --> 00:15:13,230
Give it to me.

257
00:15:13,230 --> 00:15:14,500
Don't look! Let go!

258
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,200
Wait, give it to me!

259
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,600
What's this?

260
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,930
No, she used to be my secretary.

261
00:15:19,930 --> 00:15:20,700
So...

262
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:21,770
Just conversations, nothing more.

263
00:15:21,770 --> 00:15:24,370
He called me just last night.

264
00:15:24,370 --> 00:15:25,330
Said he was engaged to you.

265
00:15:25,330 --> 00:15:26,800
It's just a fake engagement. Please calm down.

266
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,130
You calm down.

267
00:15:28,130 --> 00:15:29,600
Don't touch me! Deng Weikang!

268
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,970
What's going on?

269
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:32,500
We're already engaged!

270
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,330
Are you lying to me?

271
00:15:34,830 --> 00:15:35,970
Everyone knows we're engaged.

272
00:15:35,970 --> 00:15:37,700
And now you pull this?

273
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:38,800
So what is she to you?

274
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:41,000
Your... your girlfriend?

275
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:42,470
She was...

276
00:15:42,470 --> 00:15:43,200
She was my secretary.

277
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,730
So we... better clear things up now.

278
00:15:44,730 --> 00:15:47,130
No, secretaries naturally have conversations.

279
00:15:47,130 --> 00:15:48,100
This is Deng Weikang.

280
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:51,730
Proof that he took kickbacks from the chicken processing plant.

281
00:15:52,430 --> 00:15:54,130
That's all I know.

282
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:59,730
You didn't take this to the media or lawyers.

283
00:15:59,730 --> 00:16:01,770
Instead, you came directly to me.

284
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:04,630
What do you want?

285
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:06,930
I just want closure for my feelings.

286
00:16:06,930 --> 00:16:08,830
An explanation.

287
00:16:08,830 --> 00:16:10,200
I know.

288
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,900
The only one who can make Deng Weikang pay

289
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:14,530
is you.

290
00:16:23,430 --> 00:16:25,300
